man emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnès de Poitiers was born about 1045, in France, her father, Pierre Guillaume D AQUITAINE, was 23 and her mother, Ermesinde de Lorraine, was 13. She had at least 2 daughters with Pierre De Savoie I. She died after 18 June 1089."},"et":{"about 1045–Aft 18 June 1089":"umbes 1045–pärast 18. juunit 1089","1045–1089":"1045–1089","1060–1142":"1060–1142","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1064–1094":"1064–1094","1066–1110":"1066–1110","1023–1058":"1023–1058","1033–1058":"1033–1058","vor 1041":"enne 1041","1066":"1066","Aft 18 June 1089":"pärast 18. juunit 1089","1033":"1033","1110":"1110","1142":"1142","1064":"1064","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","9 juillet 1078":"9. juuli 1078","1058":"1058","1047":"1047","Aft 10 June 1089":"pärast 10. juunit 1089","3 November 1058":"3. november 1058","1023":"1023","1078":"1078","1089":"1089","1045":"1045","about 1058":"umbes 1058","about 1045":"umbes 1045","França":"Prantsusmaa","Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, Prantsusmaa","Savoie, Rhône-Alpes, France":"Savoie, Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Poitiers, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Poitiers, Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1045–Aft 18 June 1089":"noin 1045–18. kesäkuuta 1089 jälkeen","1045–1089":"1045–1089","1060–1142":"1060–1142","1047–1078":"1047–1078","1064–1094":"1064–1094","1066–1110":"1066–1110","1023–1058":"1023–1058","1033–1058":"1033–1058","vor 1041":"ennen vuotta